00122   typedef hash_map<int, const char *>  TextMap;
00123 
00124   TextMap &buildTextMap() {
00125     TextMap *map = new TextMap();
00126     for (int i=0; errorInfo[i].text != 0; i++)
00127       (*map)[errorInfo[i].code] = errorInfo[i].text;
00128     return *map;
00129   }

00135 const char *Error::get_text(int error) {
00136   const char *text = textMap[error];
00137   if (text == 0)
00138     return "ERROR NOT REGISTERED";
00139   return text;
00140 }

00144 std::ostream &operator<<(std::ostream &out, const Exception &e) {
00145   out << e.what() <<" - "<< Error::get_text(e.code());
00146 
00147   int prev_code = e.code();
00148 
00149   for (Exception *prev = e.prev; prev; prev = prev->prev) {
00150     out <<": "<< prev->what();
00151 
00152     if (e.code() != prev_code) {
00153       out <<" - "<< Error::get_text(e.code());
00154       prev_code = e.code();
00155     }
00156   }
00157   return out;
00158 }
